import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, x='total_casualties', y=['wounds', 'other', 'disease'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of casualties by type?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['proportion'] = data['total_casualties'] / data['total_casualties'].sum()
    plt.pie(data['proportion'], labels=data['dataset_fields'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of total casualties caused by each type?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
